    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that feels like such a cope though. like, why does it matter if a moment is \"real\" if the end result is just total cosmic erasure? if the universe is just a giant machine heading toward nothingness, then all this effort to find \"beauty\" or \"impact\" is just us lying to ourselves to avoid the truth. it's like trying to build a sandcastle right before a massive tide comes in. why even bother building it?",
